class Solution {
    public String arrangeWords(String text) {
        String[] words = text.toLowerCase().split(" ");
        Arrays.sort(words, Comparator.comparingInt(String::length));
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for (String word : words) {
            sb.append(word).append(" ");
        }
        sb.deleteCharAt(sb.length() - 1);
        sb.setCharAt(0, Character.toUpperCase(sb.charAt(0)));
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n log n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution first splits the input string into words and converts them to lowercase. It then sorts the words based on their lengths using a stable sort (Arrays.sort), preserving the original order for words of the same length. Finally, it reconstructs the sentence, capitalizing the first letter of the first word.
